{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 / G6 (Approach soundness, mechanism & alternative-selection). All correctness reasoning re-verified against the live reducer / inbound-differ / compaction code.\n\nAFFIRMATIONS:\n- G6 fitness-for-purpose: solves the NAMED problem, not a proxy. The \"Why\" correctly diagnoses why the raw-history \"ever-seen\" projection (local_label_intent) fails CLOSED across compaction; the fix moves provenance into compiled_state, which process_snapshot (src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py:515-519) blindly restores key-by-key — so \"survives compact_ticket for free\" is mechanically TRUE.\n- G6 approach selection: generated two structurally-different alternatives — (a) on-demand raw-event re-scan (the local_label_intent shape) and (b) a sidecar provenance store outside compiled_state. (a) is the very approach the plan rejects with a grounded compaction-survival argument; (b) is strictly worse on codebase-alignment + blast-radius (forfeits the existing process_snapshot/compaction/byte-parity machinery, adds reducer I/O). Chosen approach is defensibly at-least-as-good on every axis — PASS; alternatives discarded.\n- G6 concurrency/atomicity: fold + seed run inside deterministic single-threaded reducer replay, so check-then-seed is NOT a TOCTOU. Strict reducer-side monotonicity (process_unlink at :243-246 only shrinks deps) keeps the resurrection window closed.\n- G6 empty/back-out: missing managed_refs -> empty -> gate returns False (additive-only), doubling as a safe no-op back-out.\n- G6 positive rationale: PRESENT and strong (compaction-survival, single primitive, fail-safe default, explicit back-out). No rationale finding.\n\nFINDINGS (three load-bearing mechanism under-specifications):\n\n- [ ] Specify HOW the gate's CONSUMER normalizes a PEER (Jira) ref to the direction-distinguished local logical (kind, target) before the managed_refs lookup. The Jira \"Blocks\" type collapses BOTH blocks and depends_on onto one link type, disambiguated only by side: inbound_differ.py:498-502 maps a Blocks link's outward side to depends_on and inward side to blocks. managed_refs keys on direction-distinguished kinds {parent,blocks,depends_on,relates_to}, so a collapsed peer link is non-unique without an explicit normalization rule. The plan rightly puts the gate on \"local logical refs\" but never states the consumer must first resolve the collapsed peer link to the correct kind/direction — so a locally-managed depends_on could be looked up as blocks and the gate would wrongly deny (resurrect) or wrongly approve a removal.\n  criteria: [G6]\n  location: plan \"What\" / gate definition (\"operates on local logical refs\"); AC1 (\"normalized (kind, target)\"); src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/inbound_differ.py:498-502\n  evidence: inbound maps Blocks outward->depends_on, inward->blocks (line 502) — one Jira type yields two direction-distinguished local kinds; managed_refs keys on (kind,target) so a direction-collapsed peer link is non-unique without a normalization rule the plan omits.\n  suggested_fix: State in the gate contract that the consumer passes an ALREADY-normalized local logical ref (kind+direction resolved via the same inward/outward rule as inbound_differ), and add a gate unit test covering a Blocks link whose inward vs outward side maps to depends_on vs blocks.\n\n- [ ] Specify that the parent-EDIT fold captures the DISPLACED prior parent. There is no dedicated parent processor — parent changes flow through the generic last-writer-wins process_edit (src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py:319-338), which REPLACES state[field_name] (line 338) and never sees the prior value post-merge. A monotonic union of \"every parent ever managed\" therefore requires reading state[\"parent_id\"] BEFORE the merge and folding BOTH old and new parents; folding only the post-merge value silently drops the prior parent and re-opens the resurrection window for RE-PARENTED tickets. AC1 asserts the monotonic property but does not name this ordering dependency. (Also: process_edit's `if field_name not in state: continue` guard at line 328 means managed_refs cannot be folded by the generic EDIT path — it needs an explicit fold hook.)\n  criteria: [G6]\n  location: AC1 (\"folded from CREATE/LINK/parent-EDIT ... never reduced by UNLINK/detach\"); src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py:319-338 (process_edit), :56 (process_create parent_id)\n  evidence: process_edit is LWW with no dedicated parent processor — the displaced parent_id is unrecoverable once state[field_name]=new_value runs (line 338); the plan folds \"from parent-EDIT\" but does not specify pre-merge capture of the prior parent, load-bearing for the stated strictly-monotonic union.\n  suggested_fix: In the parent-EDIT fold, read state[\"parent_id\"] (old parent) BEFORE applying the merge and fold BOTH old and new (kind=parent) targets; add a unit test that re-parents A->B and asserts managed_refs contains both (parent,A) and (parent,B), and that a later detach of B still propagates.\n\n- [ ] Specify WHERE in the reduce path managed_refs seeding runs and that it executes as a post-replay finalization step (after SNAPSHOT restore AND after all post-snapshot folds), NOT inside process_snapshot. process_snapshot (:515-519) blindly copies compiled_state keys and would NOT seed an absent key; a pre-feature SNAPSHOT simply lacks managed_refs, and the seeded value must derive from the FULLY-reduced deps + parent_id (only materialized post-replay). If seeding ran at restore-time BEFORE a same-pass UNLINK, the seed-then-unlink ordering could mis-record. The plan says seeding happens \"on the FIRST reduce/restore where managed_refs is absent\" but leaves the insertion point and its ordering relative to UNLINK/fold unspecified — the exact ordering AC2's \"later unlink propagates\" depends on.\n  criteria: [G6]\n  location: plan \"Migration\" section + AC2 (\"When managed_refs is absent ... the reducer seeds it from current deps + parent_id; a test proves ... its later unlink propagates\")\n  evidence: process_snapshot (:515-519) is a blind key-copy with no seed branch; the plan leaves the hook location and ordering vs same-pass UNLINK unstated.\n  suggested_fix: State that seeding is a finalization pass over the fully-reduced state (current deps + parent_id) run after replay completes and after the monotonic folds; have the AC2 test compact under OLD code (no managed_refs key), then seed+unlink and assert propagation."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782538395354239001,"uuid":"834a021b-0a37-4aeb-9c9d-40dc304fb054"}